  "key_observation": "The price formed equal highs at 1.08800 (liquidity pool) below an unmitigated extreme supply zone, then swept that liquidity before approaching the supply zone—providing high-probability confluence for a bearish reversal.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a downtrend on EURUSD 1H with a recent bearish break of structure creating an unmitigated extreme supply zone near 1.09200–1.09400.",
    "Step 2: Observed price retracement forming equal highs at 1.08800, labeled as a liquidity pool with '$' symbols, located just below the extreme supply zone.",
    "Step 3: Confirmed a liquidity sweep occurred above the equal highs (i.e., price moved up to trigger long stop-losses), validating the setup’s confluence.",
    "Step 4: Noted the price used the prior supply zone as an inducement area and approached the extreme supply zone, setting up for a potential short entry using SMC entry models (e.g., wick/body/midpoint)."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
